<h2 The situation in the Balkans, Armenia and Arzerbaijan</h2>
"A special thought I address to the Western Balkan Region, where significant steps are being taken towards integration in the European project: ethnic, cultural and confessional differences are not a cause of division, but they become a source of wealth throughout Europe and the whole world." So Pope Francis in the Easter message before the blessing Urbi et Orbi.
&nbsp;
"Parimenti encourage the talks between Armenia and Azerbaijan, so that, with the support of the international community, they can continue dialogue, rescue the displaced, respect the places of worship of the different religious confessions and arrive as soon as possible to a definitive peace agreement," the Pontiff stressed.
&nbsp;
<h2 Thought to those who live violence, conflicts and insecurities&nbsp;</h2>
"The Risen Christ opens a way of hope to people who in other parts of the world suffer violence, conflicts, food insecurity, as well as the effects of climate change. Give comfort to the victims of all forms of terrorism." So Pope Francis in the Easter message before the blessing Urbi et Orbi. "Let us pray for those who have lost their lives and implore the repentance and conversion of the authors of such crimes," the Pontiff said.
